      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="border-top: 1px solid darkgray; padding-top: 6em; padding-bottom: 6em;" class="px-2 bg-secondary">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-10 mx-auto">
          <h2 class="h2-styles">In the news</h2>
          <h3 class="h3-styles">Unicef turns to cryptocurrency mining to raise money for refugees</h3>
          <p class="lead pb-3">
            The Independent: <a href="https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/gadgets-and-tech/news/unicef-cryptocurrency-fundraising-child-refugees-digital-bitcoin-monero-a8332726.html">Read article</a>
          </p>

          <h3 class="h3-styles">Michael Owen to launch own crypto coin</h3>
          <p class="lead pb-3">
            The Independent: <a href="https://www.independent.ie/business/technology/news/michael-owen-to-launch-own-crypto-coin-36730055.html">Read article</a>
          </p>

          <h3 class="h3-styles">HullCoin: The social experiment that is rewarding good deeds</h3>
          <p class="lead pb-3">
            Financial Times: <a href="https://www.ft.com/content/df75ff98-8904-11e7-afd2-74b8ecd34d3b">Read article</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="border-top: 1px solid darkgray; padding-top: 6em; padding-bottom: 6em;" class="px-2 bg-secondary">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-10 mx-auto">
          <h2 class="h2-styles">Supporter concerns</h2>
          <h3 class="h3-styles">Is the mining application a spyware?</h3>
          <p class="lead pb-3">
            No, nor is it a trojan or any other kind of malware. The
            app is open-source, which means anyone can view the source code
            to confirm this. The app actually consists of two programs: a graphical 
            user interface (developed by CoinFunnel), and a background 'mining process'
            which, although not developed by CoinFunnel, is also open source and 
            approved by the Monero crypto developers.
          </p>

          <h3 class="h3-styles">Will the mining application slow down my CPU?</h3>
          <p class="lead">
            No. The mining app is configured to become active only when your
            computer is idle. When you use your computer, the app will pause. 
            Additionally, the app is designed to use only 25% of your idle CPU, to
            minimise your electricty costs and to prevent against CPU burnout*.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="border-top: 1px solid darkgray; padding-top: 6em; padding-bottom: 6em;" class="px-2 bg-secondary">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-10 mx-auto">
          <h2 class="h2-styles">Charity concerns</h2>
          <h3 class="h3-styles">Isnt cryptocurrency complicated?</h3>
          <p class="lead">
            Not really. You don't need to know the mechanics of crypto to mine or 
            receive it, in the same way you don't need to understand how the Internet 
            works to use your browser.
            However, for charities there are some things that need to be learned, 
            including how to create crypto wallets into which all mining donations
            will be received. This is actually quite simple, and CoinFunnel provides 
            lots of easy-to-use information popups, simple step-by-step guides, and a temporary 
            crypto wallet to get you started.
          </p>

          <h3 class="h3-styles">Is cryptocurrency legal?</h3>
